The paper deals with human activity recognition in videos using attention-based LSTM models. This involves processing visual information and classifying actions, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of attention mechanisms and LSTM networks for classification also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves processing natural language descriptions of videos, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories.
